## Usage

1. Install all (repo-level + project-level for all projects) dependencies:
   ```bash
   uv sync --all-packages --all-extras
   ```
2. Skip dependencies of a specific project:
   ```bash
   uv sync --no-install-package <our package you want to skip>
   ```
   You can skip multiple projects by passing multiple `--no-install-package` flags.
3. Add new dependencies to specific project:
   ```bash
   uv add --package <our package> <dependency>
   ```
   Example:
   ```bash
    uv add --package ml-experiments pyyaml
    uv add --package shared.ml shared.core
    ```

## Development dependencies

This repo uses several tools to maintain code quality and consistency:

### Linter

[Ruff](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff) is used as a linter and formatter. [Editor integration](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/editors/).

To run the linter:
```shell
# highlight problems
ruff check

# highlight and fix problems
ruff check --fix
```

To run the formatter:
```shell
ruff format
```

### Type checking

[Pyright](https://github.com/microsoft/pyright) is used for static type checking. [Editor integration](https://microsoft.github.io/pyright/#/installation?id=installation) (pyright binary is stored in the venv, default path from project root: `./.venv/bin/pyright-langserver`)

To run type checking:
```shell
pyright
```

### Pre-commit hook

This project uses pre-commit hooks to ensure code quality before committing. To set up pre-commit hooks:

```shell
pre-commit install
```

Run against all files (good idea to run it once after the installation):
```shell
pre-commit run --all-files
```
